The Eiffel Tower is located in Paris, France. It is situated in the 7th arrondissement of Paris, near the Seine River. The exact address of the Eiffel Tower is Champ de Mars, 5 Avenue Anatole France, 75007 Paris, France.

The Eiffel Tower is one of the most famous landmarks in the world and is a symbol of Paris and France. It was designed by Gustave Eiffel and was completed in 1889 for the Exposition Universelle (World's Fair) to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the French Revolution.

Standing at a height of 1,063 feet (324 meters), the Eiffel Tower offers breathtaking views of the city of Paris from its three levels. Visitors can take the elevator or climb the stairs to reach the top for panoramic views of the cityscape.

Surrounded by beautiful gardens and parks, the Eiffel Tower is a must-visit attraction for tourists from around the world. It is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and a true symbol of French culture and architecture.
